# Blend2D Integration for Haiku

## Overview
Blend2D is a high-performance 2D vector graphics engine with JIT compilation capabilities.
This integration replaces the Anti-Grain Geometry (AGG) library in Haiku's graphics stack.

## License
Zlib License - Compatible with Haiku's MIT-style licensing

## Build Configuration
- Static linking (libblend2d.a)
- JIT compiler enabled for performance
- SIMD optimizations (SSE2 to AVX-512)
- Multi-threaded rendering support

## Integration Points
- Main rendering context: BLContext replaces AGG rasterizer/renderer pipeline
- Vector paths: BLPath replaces agg::path_storage
- Transformations: BLMatrix2D replaces agg::trans_affine
- Text rendering: BLFont replaces AGGTextRenderer
- Images: BLImage replaces agg::rendering_buffer

## Performance Benefits
- JIT-compiled rendering pipelines
- Modern SIMD vectorization
- Multi-threaded rendering
- Efficient memory management
- Active development and optimization

## Build Dependencies
- CMake (for upstream Blend2D build)
- C++17 compatible compiler
- Threading support (pthread on Haiku)
- No external dependencies (AsmJit embedded)